          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>
                                        <date>May 4. 5609</date>.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                                        <add>שוכ"ט לאהובי ידידי כ"ה אליעזר ח"יצו</add>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <add>נא אל יחר לאדוני לאיחרתי ע"ה מלהשיב יקרי וקבלתי
                                                  החילון</add>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <add>כי באותו הפעם הי' לי כאב</add>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>
                                        <add>עינים ולא יכולתי לכתוב ע"כ לדאקטאר מערצקאכער להודיע למה
                                                  שקבלתי החילון</add>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>N. Y.</placeName>
                                        <date>May 4, 1849</date>.</p>
                              <p>To my friend and beloved, <addressee>I liezar, Rev.</addressee><lb/>
                                        <addressee>Isaac Leeser</addressee>: Please do not be
                                        angry<lb/> that I have delayed until today to<lb/> answer
                                        your letter that I received the<lb/> exchange. For at that
                                        time I had a pain in<lb/> my eyes and I could not write. I asked<lb/>
                                        <persName>Dr. Merzbacher</persName> to let you know that
                                        I<lb/> received the exchange and then I waited<lb/>
                                        expediently for the answer of the man who<lb/> owns the
                                        Sefer Torah. He, too, answered me<lb/> asking that I send it
                                        to him. I did not<lb/> want to write to you and let you
                                        know<lb/> of this, for everyday I expected to re-<lb/>ceive
                                        it and could not understand why he delayed. Finally the
                                        man<lb/> came here this past week and told<lb/> me that he
                                        does not want to send<lb/> it in view of the fact that I
                                        know the<lb/> Sefer Torah. Unless I desire to take it<lb/>
                                        and pay $100 for it along with the ark.<lb/> Seeing that he
                                        could not be trusted, I</p>
                              <pb n="4"/>
                              <p>was very sorry to have been unable<lb/> to fulfill your request
                                        and, more so,<lb/> that I delayed the matter till now.<lb/>
                                        Then God intervened and, by a good coin-<lb/>cidence, a man
                                        arrived here and brought<lb/> this very Sefer Torah but did
                                        not want to<lb/> give it to me on commission. I took it
                                        and<lb/> paid for it with cash; since I like it so<lb/> much
                                        both from the point of view of the<lb/> writing and from the
                                        parchment. For<lb/> I can safely say there is no such
                                        writing<lb/> in the entire land. Therefore, if you<lb/> want
                                        it for $90. please let me know,<lb/> and if not, be good
                                        enough to<lb/> return it to me at once, for I have<lb/>
                                        another customer for it who will<lb/> probably arrive next
                                        week.</p>
                              <p>If you want to give me some<lb/> books on commission, both Hebrew
                                        and<lb/> English, especially prayer books and<lb/>
                                        Pentateuchs, as cheaply as possible, I should</p>
                              <pb n="5"/>
                              <p>be pleased. Perhaps I shall be able to<lb/> earn something. The
                                        first part of the<lb/> Torah being written by <persName>Mr.
                                                  Ettinger</persName>, the scribe,<lb/> will be
                                        looked over by me on <date>Sunday</date> next,<lb/> since
                                        this time I have more leisure. Please<lb/> let me know
                                        whether the article written in Eng-<lb/>lish about the
                                        meeting which took place in<lb/>
                                        <date>June</date> and which is signed by you, was sent<lb/>
                                        to my address, or don't you know anything<lb/> about it? I
                                        have to make it short be-<lb/>cause of a wedding which is to
                                        take place in<lb/> my house, although I have more to
                                        say.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">Your friend,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">
                                        <persName role="author">Schneor Nusbaum</persName>
                              </p>
                    </body>
